Foreign investors purchased, on a netbasis, a record one billion dlrs of Canadian stocks inFebruary, more than the total for all of 1986, StatisticsCanada said.    U.S. residents continued to be the largest investor, withpurchases doubling from the previous month to more than 800 mlndlrs.    Net sales of outstanding Canadian bonds to Japan, however,amounted to 679 mln dlrs in February, which, on average, wasabout 500 mln less than in each of the four previous months. Reuter&#3;